# Leaf Design System - Project Rules

This project uses the **Leaf Design System** (`@herbalifedev/leaf`) from Herbalife. Always prefer Leaf components over raw HTML or custom implementations.

## Typography

**Use the `Text` component for all text content.** Never use raw `<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<p>`, or `<span>` for styled text.

```jsx
// ❌ BAD - raw HTML
<h1 className="lf:font-display lf:text-(--lf-heading-color)">Title</h1>
<p className="lf:text-(--lf-paragraph-color)">Description</p>

// ✅ GOOD - Leaf Text component
import { Text } from '@herbalifedev/leaf'

<Text type="heading" size="xlarge" className="lf:text-(--lf-heading-color)">
  Title
</Text>
<Text type="paragraph" size="medium" className="lf:text-(--lf-description-color)">
  Description
</Text>
```

### Text Component API

| type       | sizes                          | Use case                    |
|-----------|---------------------------------|-----------------------------|
| `heading` | xlarge, large, medium, small, xsmall | Section titles, headings   |
| `paragraph` | xlarge, large, medium, small | Body text, descriptions    |
| `display` | xlarge, large                   | Hero text, large headlines  |
| `caption` | —                               | Labels, metadata            |
| `small-title` | large, medium, small         | Card titles, small headings |

### Heading size mapping (design tokens)

- `xlarge` → `--lf-heading-1`
- `large` → `--lf-heading-2`
- `medium` → `--lf-heading-3`
- `small` → `--lf-heading-4`
- `xsmall` → `--lf-heading-5`

## Components

Import from `@herbalifedev/leaf`:

- **Text** – typography
- **Button**, **OutlinedButton** – actions
- **InputText**, **InputPassword**, etc. – form inputs
- **SimpleCard**, **Tag** – content blocks
- **Brand** – Herbalife branding
- **Icon** – icons (when needed)

## Styling conventions

1. **Prefix all Leaf-related classes with `lf:`** (e.g. `lf:flex`, `lf:bg-(--lf-bg-1)`).
2. **Use design tokens** for colors, spacing, and typography:
   - Colors: `--lf-heading-color`, `--lf-paragraph-color`, `--lf-description-color`, `--lf-primary-color`, `--lf-bg-1`, `--lf-bg-2`, `--lf-border-muted`
   - Shapes: `--lf-shape-card`
3. **Avoid hardcoded values** when a design token exists.

## Checklist for new UI

- [ ] Use `Text` instead of raw headings/paragraphs
- [ ] Use Leaf components (Button, InputText, etc.) instead of custom elements
- [ ] Apply `lf:` prefix to Tailwind classes
- [ ] Use design tokens for colors and spacing
